# Deliberately EMPTY of LFS rules — do not re-add `*.tflite filter=lfs`.
#
# The two moderation models (app/src/main/assets/moderation/{nsfw,toxicity}.tflite, ~32 MB total) are
# stored as ordinary Git blobs because F-Droid's buildserver has no Git LFS support (fdroidserver issue
# #1190, open since 2024). A checkout without a working LFS client yields 130-byte pointer stubs, and
# NsfwImageModerator / MlTextModerator both degrade *silently* to allow-all on an unreadable model — so
# LFS here means F-Droid would ship a quietly unmoderated app that also fails reproducible-build
# verification. Plain blobs make that impossible; the build additionally hard-fails on a stub model
# (see the checkModerationModels task in app/build.gradle.kts).
